      "rationale": "Three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary outputs specified in ASTM F1717 and directly correspond to the clinical failure modes of interest: fatigue fracture and permanent deformation. These QoIs are explicitly referenced in the 510(k) submission protocol and are the decision-relevant outputs for the intended regulatory use."
